the counseling & psychological services (caps) office is on the third floor of the student wellness center in room 300b. the student wellness center is located at the corner of 7th and san carlos, across from the event center.if you have an emergency and need immediate assistance during our hours of operation, there is always a staff member available to assist you either on the phone or in person. call 408-924-5910.for after-hours emergencies, please call 911. if you live on campus, please call campus police at 408-924-2222. you may also call our main number 408-924-5910 after hours and press 4 to connect with the after-hours crisis service.the county suicide & crisis line is also available at 855-278-4204 (toll-free) 24/7.or call the national suicide prevention lifeline at 1-800-273-talk (8255). this service is also available 24/7.in addition, you may send a text for help to 741741. the crisis call center will respond 24/7/365. they will help get you through it.you may also call the after-hours advice nurse regarding medication questions 866-935-6347.you can schedule an appointment by calling us at 408-924-5910 or stopping by counseling and psychological services during business hours. we are located on the 3floor of the student wellness center.appointments are available forpersonal counselingandcase managementservices.if you feel that you need to speak with a counselor immediately, you may utilize ourcrisis interventionservices.for the summer 2022 semester, caps provides services through telehealth with limited in-person services. caps office is physically open mondays through friday from 8:30 am - 4:30 pm. we will also have confidential rooms available if students need a space for their telehealth appointments.students must log into thestudent patient portaland check in to initiate your zoom appointment.please check in 30 minutes before your appointment on the portal and complete any necessary forms before you start your zoom appointment.if you are having any issues with accessing the appointment and forms, please call us at (408) 924-5910.phone:408-924-5910fax: 408-924-5933email:counseling.services@sjsu.educounseling and psychological servicessan jos state universityone washington square,swc 300bsan jose, ca 95192-0035student wellness center (swc)3rd floor, room 300bmonday - thursday: 8:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.friday (march 31): closedmonday - thursday: 8:30 a.m. to 5:00 p.m.friday: 8:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.